    "The starting point is Zero-Shot Learning results from MistralAI [37] and corrected by the experts.",
    "This may add to a bias when deciding if the model is correct, but it is required to speed up the process.",
    "Chapter 4 Results Comparative Analysis Baseline Model and Continued TrainingThe RoBERTa-Large engine serves as the baseline, demonstrating strong precision in relevance labeling but showing limitations in the prediction of the downstream labels.",
    "Although models derived from continued RoBERTa training generally do not show improvements over the baseline, this trend is notably reversed with the EconRoBERTa-Large-R8 model in the context of downstream labels.",
    "This suggests that the marginal gains achieved through continued training may not justify the associated environmental and computational costs."
